Idibus Maiis: this fixes the date of the letter as later than May 15. — rogatus sententiam: the technical expression used of the action of the presiding consul in asking senators their views on the question before the senate. The rules of the Roman senate allowed a senator to depart from the special topic under considera- tion, and de summa republica dicere.
